WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:30.402 --> 00:37.032
the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ, a sermon by Charles Spurgeon, part 4.

00:38.595 --> 00:51.135
For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, hath shined in our hearts to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

00:51.155 --> 00:55.602
2 Corinthians chapter 4 verse 6.

00:57.825 --> 00:58.386
Thirdly,

00:58.690 --> 01:02.053
Let us gratefully review the means of this knowledge.

01:03.114 --> 01:04.315
How have we come at it?

01:05.917 --> 01:18.529
That brings us to read the text again, for God who commanded the light to shine out of darkness hath shined in our hearts to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

01:19.731 --> 01:24.555
Why did not everybody see the glory of God in Jesus Christ when he was here?

01:25.736 --> 01:27.378
It was conspicuous enough.

01:28.514 --> 01:33.361
Answer, it matters not how brightly the sun shines among the blind.

01:34.843 --> 01:36.906
Now the human heart is blind.

01:37.567 --> 01:42.253
It refuses to see God in creation, except after a dim fashion.

01:43.215 --> 01:46.840
But it utterly refuses to discern God in Christ.

01:47.981 --> 01:52.287
And therefore he is the despised and rejected by men and women.

01:53.489 --> 01:57.074
Moreover, there is a God of this world, the Prince of Darkness,

01:57.570 --> 02:07.039
And since he hates the light, he deepens and confirms the natural darkness of the human mind, lest the light should reach the heart.

02:08.080 --> 02:21.853
He blinds people's minds with error and falsehood and foul imaginations, blocking up the windows of the soul, either with unclean desires or with dense ignorance or with pride.

02:22.994 --> 02:27.538
The reason why we did not at one time perceive the glory of God in Christ,

02:28.002 --> 02:32.929
was because we were blind by nature and were darkened by the evil one.

02:34.431 --> 02:42.241
As only the pure in heart can see God, we being impure in heart could not see God in Christ.

02:43.543 --> 02:52.996
What then hath happened to us, to eternal grace be endless praise, God Himself hath shined into our hearts.

02:54.017 --> 02:57.362
That same God who said light be.

02:58.082 --> 03:01.686
and light was, hath shined into our hearts.

03:02.908 --> 03:07.473
You know, creation's story, how all things lay in darkness.

03:08.635 --> 03:12.500
God might have gone on to make a world in darkness if he had pleased.

03:13.401 --> 03:20.109
But if he had done so, it would have been to us as though it had never been, for we could not have perceived it.

03:21.170 --> 03:24.434
And therefore he early said, let there be light.

03:25.986 --> 03:33.673
Now God's glory in the face of Jesus Christ might have been all there, and we should never have discerned it.

03:34.634 --> 03:38.698
And as far as we are concerned, it would have been as though it had never been.

03:38.738 --> 03:54.834
If the Lord had not entered into us amid the thick darkness and said, Let there be light, then burst in the everlasting morning, the light shined in the darkness.

03:54.978 --> 03:57.401
and the darkness fled before it.

03:58.763 --> 04:01.767
Do you recollect the incoming of that illumination?

04:02.708 --> 04:10.219
If you do, then I know the first sight you saw by the new light was the glory of God in Jesus Christ.

04:11.340 --> 04:15.686
In fact, the light had come on purpose that you might see it.

04:16.667 --> 04:24.658
And at this present moment, that is the main delight of your soul, the choice subject of your thoughts.

04:25.634 --> 04:30.119
In the light of God, you have seen the light of the glory of God.

04:31.220 --> 04:35.185
As it is written, In thy light, we shall see light.

04:36.467 --> 04:44.256
One thing I want to say to comfort all who believe, Beloved, do you see the glory of God in Christ Jesus?

04:45.297 --> 04:49.402
Then let that sight be an evidence to you of your salvation.

04:50.903 --> 04:53.266
When our Lord asked His disciples

04:53.346 --> 04:55.929
Whom do men say that I, the Son of Man am?

04:57.512 --> 05:03.239
Simon Peter answered, Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.

05:04.681 --> 05:07.986
Now note the reply of the Lord Jesus to that confession.

05:09.127 --> 05:18.039
Blessed art thou, Simon Barjona, for flesh and blood have not revealed it unto you, but my Father which is in heaven.

05:19.361 --> 05:23.186
If thou can't delight in God in Christ Jesus, then remember,

05:23.554 --> 05:28.320
No man can say that Jesus is the Christ but by the Holy Spirit.

05:29.482 --> 05:36.310
And thou hast said it, and this morning thou art saying it, and therefore the Holy Spirit has come upon thee.

05:37.672 --> 05:42.739
Whosoever believeth that Jesus is the Christ is born of God.

05:44.000 --> 05:48.266
Thou believeth this, and therefore thou art born of the Father.

05:49.407 --> 05:51.410
Whosoever denyeth the Son,

05:51.714 --> 05:58.726
The same hath not the Father, but he that acknowledges the Son hath the Father also.

05:59.888 --> 06:02.432
Thou lovest God, and thou art his.

06:03.093 --> 06:07.941
The Spirit of God hath opened thine eyes, and thou art saved."

06:09.224 --> 06:15.474
So I finish by mentioning in the fourth place the responsibilities of this knowledge.

06:16.802 --> 06:22.771
There have been considerable debates among the interpreters as to the precise bearing of this text.

06:23.672 --> 06:28.520
And some of them think it means that Paul is giving a reason why he preached the gospel.

06:29.862 --> 06:46.066
This makes the verse run thus, for God who commanded the light to shine out of darkness hath shined in our hearts that we might give out again the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

06:47.170 --> 06:55.821
God gave light to the apostles that they might show forth the light of the knowledge of God in the face of Jesus Christ to the nations.

06:57.263 --> 07:03.111
I do not know whether this is the exact run of the text, but I know it is true anyhow.

07:04.553 --> 07:14.706
Never is the gleam of light given to any man to hide away and to spiritual men the great object of their lives after they have received light.

07:15.298 --> 07:18.322
is to reflect that light in all its purity.

07:19.743 --> 07:22.607
You must not hoard up the light within yourself.

07:23.768 --> 07:25.931
It will not be light to you if you do.

07:25.951 --> 07:37.946
Only think of a person when his room is full of sunlight saying to his servant, quick now, close the shutters and let us keep this precious light to ourselves.

07:39.327 --> 07:41.931
Your room will be in the dark, my friend.

07:43.192 --> 07:44.754
So when a child of God

07:44.834 --> 07:46.897
gets the light from Christ's face.

07:47.518 --> 07:50.082
He must not say, I shall keep this to myself.

07:50.803 --> 07:52.926
For that very desire would shut it out.

07:54.247 --> 07:56.391
No, let the light shine through you.

07:57.392 --> 07:58.914
Let it shine everywhere.

08:00.156 --> 08:02.740
You have the light that you may reflect it.

08:03.721 --> 08:07.907
An object which absorbs light is dark and we call it black.

08:09.009 --> 08:12.754
But hang up a reflector in its place when the sun is shining.

08:13.218 --> 08:14.940
and it will not appear black.

08:15.861 --> 08:19.284
It will be so bright that you will hardly bear to look at it.

08:20.686 --> 08:28.414
An object is itself bright in proportion as it sends back the light which it receives.

08:28.434 --> 08:34.601
So you shall find, as a Christian, that if you absorb light into yourself, you will be black.

08:35.522 --> 08:39.506
But if you scatter it abroad, you yourself shall be brilliant.

08:40.770 --> 08:44.755
You shall be changed into the very image of the light which you have received.

08:45.456 --> 08:47.879
You shall become a second sun."

08:49.661 --> 09:09.106
I noticed last Sabbath evening when I came into this pulpit that at the angle of the building before me on the left hand the sun seemed to be setting, and I saw the brightness of his round face, and yet I knew it to be the wrong quarter of the heavens for the sun to be setting there.

09:10.242 --> 09:23.699
Perhaps you will observe that there is a peculiar window on the other side of the street, and it was reflecting the sun so well that I thought it was the sun himself, and I could hardly bear the light.

09:24.660 --> 09:30.087
It was not the sun, it was only a window, and yet the radiance was dazzling.

09:31.449 --> 09:39.058
And so a man of God, when he receives the light of Christ, can become so perfect a reflector

09:39.586 --> 09:43.670
that to common eyes at any rate, He is brightness itself.

09:44.371 --> 09:50.757
He has become transformed from glory to glory, as by the image of the Lord.

09:52.819 --> 10:08.114
Brothers and sisters, if you have learned the truth, manifest it and make it plain to others, proclaim the gospel, not your own thoughts, for it is Christ that you are to make manifest.

10:08.706 --> 10:17.034
Teach not your own judgments and conclusions and opinions, but the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

10:17.855 --> 10:20.898
Let Jesus manifest Himself in His own light.

10:22.059 --> 10:26.884
Do not cast a light on Him or attempt to show the sun with a candle.

10:28.346 --> 10:36.914
Do not aim at converting men and women to your views, but let the light shine for itself and work its own way.

10:37.698 --> 10:49.150
Do not colour it by being like a painted window to it, but let the clear white light shine through you that others may behold your Lord.

10:51.333 --> 10:54.116
Scatter your light in all unselfishness.

10:55.177 --> 11:07.090
Wish to shine, not that others may say how bright he is, but that they, getting the light, may rejoice in the source from which it came to you and to them.

11:08.354 --> 11:13.460
be willing to make every sacrifice to spread this light which you have received.

11:14.721 --> 11:21.408
consecrate your entire being to the making known among the whole world the glory of Christ.

11:22.890 --> 11:29.958
Oh, I would we had swift messengers to run the world over to tell the story that God has come down among us.

11:30.979 --> 11:37.586
I wish we had fluent tongues to tell in every language the story that coming down among us

11:37.858 --> 11:44.769
God was arrayed in flesh like to our own, and that He took our sins and carried our sorrows.

11:45.911 --> 12:01.116
Oh, that we had trumpet tongues to make the message peel through heaven and earth, that God has come among men, and cries come unto me, all ye that labour and are heavy laden, and I will give you rest.

12:02.218 --> 12:04.882
Oh, for a thunder voice to speak it,

12:05.506 --> 12:23.183
or a lightning pen to write it across the heavens, that God has reconciled the world unto Himself by the death of His Son, not imputing their trespasses unto them, and that whosoever believes in Christ Jesus has everlasting life.

12:24.764 --> 12:29.469
I cannot command thunder or lightning, but here are your tongues.

12:30.630 --> 12:32.772
Go and tell it this afternoon.

12:33.773 --> 12:34.994
Here is my tongue.

12:35.618 --> 12:51.322
and I have tried to tell it, and may it be silent in the dust of death er it ceases to declare that one blessed message, that God in Christ Jesus receives the sons of men in boundless love.

12:52.844 --> 12:58.633
Tell it, brother, with broken accents, if you cannot speak it more powerfully.

12:59.854 --> 13:02.258
Whisper it, sister, gently whisper,

13:02.882 --> 13:05.967
if to none other yet to your own little children.

13:07.149 --> 13:12.938
And make the name of Emmanuel God with us to be sweet in your infancy as.

13:14.541 --> 13:17.105
You are growing in strength and talent, young man.

13:17.666 --> 13:20.110
Come, consecrate yourself to this.

13:20.150 --> 13:30.386
And you with grey beard, when you lie down on your last bed to breathe out your spirit, tell the love of Jesus to your children.

13:30.850 --> 13:52.114
that they may tell it to their children and hand it down to coming generations, that humanity may never forget that the word was made flesh and dwelt among us, and we beheld His glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father, full of grace and truth.

13:53.676 --> 13:55.698
God bless you, Amen.

13:57.698 --> 13:59.001
Thank you for listening, friends.

13:59.302 --> 14:04.073
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

14:04.675 --> 14:12.754
